{
  "texts": [
    "The mean sentiment scores from VADER (0.175) and AFINN (0.346) indicate a mild positive bias in AI-related headlines.",
    "In contrast, TextBlob's mean score (-0.040) highlights a slightly negative sentiment, mildly pointing to the presence of caution and skepticism.",
    "The wide range of sentiment scores (from strongly negative to strongly positive) across all tools underscores the polarized nature of AI news headlines, reflecting diverse perspectives ranging from enthusiasm to uncertainty and fear.",
    "xx Results -Topic Modeling with BERTopicIn our study, we applied BERTopic (76) to analyze 67,091 headlines related to AI news.",
    "This analysis, enhanced by the c-TF-IDF method for keyword extraction and further enriched through the Nocodefunctions App for semantic network creation, enabled us to visualize and understand the relationships between key concepts across the data."
  ]
